#Text=Harris County Does
#Text=The Harris County Does consist of two currently unidentified youths discovered on January 12 , 1981 in Houston , Harris County , Texas near Wallisville Road .
#Text=Extensive investigation has been conducted with few leads . [ 1 ]
#Text=Victims
#Text=Both victims , a male and female , were found murdered , approximately eight weeks to two months before , between November and December 1980 . [ 1 ] [ 2 ] [ 3 ]
#Text=Although their weights were impossible to estimate and the faces were not recognizable due to decomposition , their fingerprints , dental records and DNA were taken . [ 2 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=Both of their bodies were hidden on private property in the woods around 100 yards from the road and later found by a dog . [ 5 ] [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=They were both buried in indigent graves near to the then-unidentified Michelle Garvey , who was later identified and transported to Connecticut in 2014 . [ 6 ] [ 5 ]
#Text=Female victim
#Text=The female , who was white with a possible Native American - admixture , was between the ages of eighteen and twenty five , although she may have been as young as fifteen . [ 3 ]
#Text=The cause of her death was ruled to be strangulation . [ 7 ]
#Text=She was estimated to have been around five feet four inches to five feet nine inches tall .
#Text=Her hair was eighteen inches long and reddish-brown , styled in a ponytail .
#Text=Her eyes were believed to have been brown and both of her ears were likely pierced , although only one earring was found in her right ear . [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=She had excellent dental hygiene , as did her companion . [ 5 ]
#Text=The victim was found near a pair of green jogging shorts and a " bloody towel " and no clothing was found on her body . [ 7 ]
#Text=What are considered to be identifying factors for the girl is that she likely had an abnormal amount of hair on her face and she had a gap between her two front teeth . [ 1 ]
#Text=The victim was presumably a nail biter , as her fingernails were noticeably short . [ 8 ]
#Text=Her wisdom teeth were emerging at the time of death . [ 3 ]
#Text=Nine missing people from Texas and one from Pennsylvania have been ruled out as possible identities of the female . [ 2 ]
#Text=Male victim
#Text=The male was somewhat older , estimated to be twenty to thirty years old , although he could have been as young as fifteen . [ 1 ]
#Text=Like the female , he was also white , had brown eyes and brown hair , although it was wavy and six inches long .
#Text=The male was around five feet four to five feet eight inches tall at the time of his murder , which had been committed through beating . [ 9 ] [ 7 ]
#Text=Unlike the female , he was bound and gagged . [ 5 ]
#Text=He had prominent eyebrows and some deterioration of some of his upper vertebrae in the neck region , possibly the result of an injury in the past or the presence of an abnormal joint . [ 4 ]

#Text=As for dentals , one filling was found in one of the molars ; he also had restorations and his upper wisdom teeth were not found , as they may have been removed or they may not have developed . [ 10 ]
#Text=Six missing men were ruled out as possible identities for the male victim . [ 9 ]
